"Machine learning models only understand math, so text must be converted to numbers. For ordinal variables (like quality ratings where 'Excellent' is clearly better than 'Fair'), I mapped them directly to numerical scales from 0 to 5. For nominal variables without a natural rank (like Neighborhood), I used One-Hot Encoding (pd.get_dummies), creating separate 1 or 0 binary columns for each category so the algorithm can process them mathematically without assuming an artificial order."
